	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>NES/Famicom board - just an idea</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Don't know if it is any original, it is just got into my head, and I thought to post it here. Currently there are separate boards for NES and Famicom. What if they will be combined into one? Like, two side connectors, one at top, other at bottom, two sets of holes, so the same board could be put into a NES cart case, or flipped and put into a Famicom cart case (possibly with cutting off unneeded pieces).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
